<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTERS AND COOLER - OIL COOLER AND
        COOLANT FILTER HEADER ASSEMBLY - INSPECTION AND REPAIR
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSPECTION AND REPAIR</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Construct two plates, as illustrated in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150936">9.36</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ; one with 1/4" NPT hole and one without.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>USE ADEQUATE SAFETY PRECAUTIONS WHEN PERFORMING THE FOLLOWING TEST.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten the plates, using new oil cooler gaskets, to the oil cooler.</para>
            <figure id="ef4150936" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12292" filename="../figcg1/CG12292.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.36. Pressure Plate Fabrication.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a regulated air supply to the pressure plate fitting. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_204.xml" xrefid="ef4150937">9.37</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Immerse the assembly in a container of water, heated to 120&#176; F (49&#176; C).</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The heated water stabilizes the metal parts of the cooler.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply 150 psi (935 kPa) air pressure while immersed in the water tank</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Visually inspect the cooler for moving or growing bubbles after one minute.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The oil cooler cannot be repaired. If bubbling is found, replace the oil cooler.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
